dc_description_s: Relief shown pictorially. Border of map includes views of cities, costumes, and arms of German principalities. Illustrations include cherubs with fruit and a chalice around the title cartouche and ships on the ocean. From "Atlantis maioris appendix", Johannes Janssonius, 1630. 1 map; 34 x 46 cm. This map is in the public domain. Please attribute access and use of this digitized map to the Stephen S. Clark Library, University of Michigan Library.
dc_title_s: Germaniae: post omnes in hoc forma; Claes Janssen Visscher.; Germania;Germany
